arch:property.oc:show_val: The west architectural niche is also open and provided a space for vessels to draw water. The architectural niche is two rows in depth and 12 courses in height. The first two days of excavation were exclusively concerned with clearing this area, thus the majority of the soil loci were determined in a small area without latitude to properly examine the balk.

Phase VI: Late Nabataean pre CE 106 minor collapses and repairs. Probable early collapse of the Baroque Room and damage occurs in both the Anteroom and Shrine Room. The tabun in Room A is used to store CE 1st c. Nabataean fine wares. East 'Cistern" used as a dump. Bath Complex built.
The interior dimensions: 0.70 m north south-by- 0.40 m east west.
The west architectural boundary of the Trench.
Construction of the Well Room and the canalization system.
